From: Bill Wendling <>
Subject: [patch-2.3.47] Removal of <linux/lists.h> and <linux/dlist.h>
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/2/23/43

Hi,
Here's a patch which removes the <linux/dlists.h> file and changes the
kernel/sysctl.c file so that it uses the <linux/list.h> linked list
instead of <linux/lists.h>'s linked list. The patch is below and also
available at:
http://ganymede.isdn.uiuc.edu/~wendling/patches/patch-2.3.47-1.list_enh
-- 
|| Bill Wendling			wendling@ganymede.isdn.uiuc.edu
